Dear Team,

Please find below the module-wise status of SPINRISE ahead of today's 5 
PM review meeting, along with a process change effective from Monday 13 
April.

*WORKING CALENDAR — NEXT WEEK*

Monday 13 April: First working day.
Tuesday 14 April: Leave — Tamil New Year Eve.
Wednesday 15, Thursday 16, Friday 17 April: Working days.
Saturday 18 April: 3rd Saturday — non-working holiday.

We have only 4 working days next week. The next Saturday review is 25 
April. To maintain momentum despite the short week, I am scheduling the 
next review meeting for Friday 17 April at 5 PM. Going forward, we will 
hold one review meeting every week — on Friday evenings where Saturday 
is a holiday, and on Saturday evenings otherwise.

*I will ask each module leader to share their committed completion dates 
for their open items at today's meeting. *The targets below are not 
imposed — they are placeholders to be confirmed or revised by the team 
this evening.

*M01 — Purchase Order: Purchase Requisition Form*
Developer: Mariyaiya | IST: Muthuvel | TL-IST: Palanivel

This is the most advanced FSD in the project. FSD v2.1 has all 20 IST 
questions resolved, Stage 0 complete, Zero CustID blocks confirmed, nine 
defects documented, and the po_para 63-column analysis incorporated. 
Mariyaiya and Muthuvel have done commendable work reaching this stage.

Four short additions remain for CEO approval: Stage 0 sign-off in the 
Document Identity header, po_para audit result in Section 13 Q19, TC=1 
rate override marked as dead code in Section 5, and Remarks varchar(50) 
truncation flagged as a Critical Defect in Section 12. Mariyaiya, please 
complete these before 5 PM today.

One IST blocker remains: the web approval screen URL. Palanivel, this 
has been asked three times. Please bring it to this evening's meeting.

If both conditions are met tonight: First CEO-approved FSD in SPINRISE. 
Sprint 0 begins Monday 13 April.


*M02 — Raw Material Inventory: RMI Purchase Order*
Developer: TL-Dev Sasi | IST: PM Saravanan | TL-IST: Palanivel

This FSD has the strongest technical foundation of the four. Stage 0 
confirmed. TC Framework with full GL journal sets the project standard. 
All 10 IST questions answered. Sasi's work here reflects TL-Dev-level 
depth — acknowledged.

One critical section is missing: Section 5.11, the PR-to-PO conversion 
workflow. This is the primary daily operation for this screen and cannot 
be absent from the FSD. SP_PRToPO_RMI and SP_PRToPO_RMIFilter codes also 
need to be submitted to Claude via Follow-up Prompt B. Saravanan, the 
web approval screen URL is pending for M02 as well.

Sasi and Saravanan to commit to completion dates this evening.


*M03 — Domestic Sales: Sale Order*
Developer: Annamalai | IST: Seenivasan | TL-IST: Palanivel

Annamalai's v1 to v2 revision was a significant improvement. 
Seenivasan's Round 2 IST responses were factual and actionable. The CSM 
Phase 2 decision simplifies Phase 1 scope meaningfully.

The most critical open question: Stage 0 is not confirmed. Section 11 
lists 11 customer-specific CustID-based variations and the FSD itself 
rates Customer Configurability at 3 out of 5. SPINRISE cannot be built 
from a form with hardcoded customer ID checks. Annamalai must confirm 
with TL-Dev Sasi whether Stage 0 is complete on frmcontract.frm and 
whether the CustID blocks have been replaced with ig_param flags. This 
is the gating item for M03.

Three SP codes not yet submitted, audit trail missing from Section 8.3, 
document number race condition not flagged as Critical Defect. 
Seenivasan has two short follow-up answers outstanding.

Annamalai and Seenivasan to commit to completion dates this evening.


*M04 — HR and Payroll: Daily Attendance Download*
Developer: Sathiskumar | IST: Palanivel

Sathiskumar's first draft was a strong submission with 14 sections and 
detailed SP analysis. Stage 0 is not yet confirmed in the document 
header. Seven IST items remain open. KSP_AttendanceTransferDate SP code 
has not been submitted to Claude. Two screen names (weekly-off exception 
review, OT approval) are pending from Palanivel.

Reminder: priority for M04 is the payroll transaction forms — salary 
processing, deductions, leave encashment — over the attendance download 
form.

Sathiskumar and Palanivel to commit to completion dates this evening.


*SPRINT 0*

Sprint 0 begins once at least one FSD has CEO approval. M01 is the 
candidate for tonight. Claude Code usage on any SPINRISE form is 
permitted only after CEO approval of that form's FSD.


*NEW: FSD REVIEW CHECKLIST — MANDATORY FROM MONDAY 13 APRIL*

The detailed checklist is attached as a Word file. Please download, 
read, and keep it at hand.

In brief, the checklist covers five stages:

Stage 0 (Developer + TL-Dev): Code cleaning, CustID block removal, line 
count confirmation, TL-Dev sign-off.
Stage 1 (Developer): Complete 14-section FSD draft with SP code 
analysis, exact error messages, parameter flags with SPINRISE defaults, 
and Critical Defects with specific fixes.
Stage 2 (Module Sr IST): Section 13 answers from personal field 
experience — minimum 5 support patterns for IST-4, approval screen name 
for IST-2, no 'developer confirmed' or 'should be' answers.
Stage 3 (TL-IST Palanivel): Independent review with own commentary — not 
a forward, not bare 'Yes, I agreed' responses.
Stage 4 (PM Saravanan): Quality gate before CEO — verify IST answers are 
current-state, confirm all sections complete, name specific gaps in any 
rejection.
Stage 5 (CEO): Final approval, locked baseline, Sprint authorisation.

 From Monday 13 April: no submission at any stage will be accepted 
without the corresponding checklist section completed and signed. The PM 
will return any submission that arrives without it.

This is not additional bureaucracy. *It is the single change that will 
reduce the multi-round correction cycles and get each FSD to approval in 
one clean pass.
*
See you all at 5 PM today.

Regards,
T. Mani

Attachment: SPINRISE_FSD_Review_Checklist_v1.0.docx

To: Sasi, Mariyaiya, Abinandan, Annamalai, Sathiskumar, PM Saravanan, 
Muthuvel, Seenivasan, TL-IST Palanivel, Hariharan

